âœ… Steps to Complete the Task

Install Android Studio (Electric Eel or newer to avoid Backpack rendering bugs).

Create a New Project

Template: Empty Activity

Language: Kotlin

Min SDK: API 33 (Tiramisu)

Run Your App Once to verify the emulator works.

Add Backpack Dependency In app/build.gradle:

dependencies { implementation 'net.skyscanner.backpack:backpack-android:43.0.0' }

Sync Gradle.

Build the UI in res/layout/activity_main.xml:

A Flight Info Card (with flight number).

A Departure Card (with 3-digit airport code + departure time).

An Arrival Card (with 3-digit airport code + arrival time).

Use BpkCardView and BpkText components styled with Backpack.

Example snippet for one card:

<net.skyscanner.backpack.card.BpkCardView android:layout_width="match_parent" android:layout_height="wrap_content" app:cornerStyle="large">

<LinearLayout
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
    android:orientation="vertical"
    android:padding="16dp">

    <net.skyscanner.backpack.text.BpkText
        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="Flight BA123"
        style="@style/bpkTextHeading1"/>
</LinearLayout>
</net.skyscanner.backpack.card.BpkCardView>

Test on Emulator Run the app, ensure cards display dummy data properly.

Push to GitHub

Initialize git:

git init git add . git commit -m "Flightscry UI PoC with Backpack"

Create a new repo at https://github.com/new .

Link and push:

git remote add origin https://github.com/<username>/flightscry-poc.git git branch -M main git push -u origin main

Submit Repo Link Example format:

https://github.com/ nandkishorsahu-code/flightscry-poc

